{
  "texts": [
    "By modifying a gating structure of a traditional RNN model, the LSTM model can learn or retain a longer data sequence.",
    "Therefore, LSTM has three gates: input, forget, and hidden.",
    "An LSTM unit with these three gates and a memory cell forms a layer of neural network neurons, and each neuron has a hidden layer and a current state.",
    "Figure 4 shows the LSTM cell's structural layout.The forget gate is used to specify whether or not certain data will be kept.",
    "This preservation is accomplished using the following formula;f t ¼ rðW f ½h tÀ1; x t þ b f Þwhere x t denotes input at time t, h tÀ1 denotes the output of previous cell, and r is a sigmoid function."
  ]
}